div.p:
Pyrrhus ſaid he woone more cities by the induſtrie of his Oratour Cineas, then he took by force of arms;
Plut. in Pyrrh. Let our faithfull preaching the word without minſing or ſingularitie, or Popiſh and falſe allegations againſt thoſe bleſſed men of God, Calvin, Beza, & the reſt, win more ſoules, then the circumventing ſtratagems of the Ieſuits. Let me ſpeake to you Nobly and Honourably deſcended flowers of this garden of the muſes,
To the hopefull ſonnes of the Honorab. The L. Montegle, The L. Peter, The L. Spenſer. Sr Robert Carey the Paradiſe of God, ſonnes of ſo worthy Fathers. Seaſon your ſtudies with the reading of the word, Let not the booke of the Law depart out of your hands, meditate in it day and night. Let the Poet encourage you.
